  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A great beginner crag just outside Eskilstuna with short, easy bolted routes. The rock is boulder-like, featuring plenty of ledges, cracks, edges and jugs. Route lengths range from 10 to 15 metres, and most routes have solid anchors.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:tumbo"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A great beginner crag just outside Eskilstuna with short and easy bolted routes. The rock is blocky, featuring plenty of ledges, cracks, seams, and jugs. Route lengths vary between 10 and 15 meters. Most routes have solid anchors.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Environment",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The routes are divided into four sectors. The blocky surroundings make it a bit tricky to move between sections, especially when wet. Watch out for adders. Most routes are in shade and are unlikely to dry quickly after rain. The area in the right section is suitable for a camping spot (no tents allowed).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag is located a few kilometres from Tumbo, beneath an ancient fortress. Drive E20 from Eskilstuna towards Örebro/Göteborg. Turn towards Västerås (road 53). At the first roundabout, follow the sign towards Tumbo (3km). Turn left towards Arbåga (in the centre of the village, but before the church). After 800 meters, a small gravel road turns left. About 20 meters along this road, there's a small sign \"Fornborg 0.2\". Parking for two cars is possible at a road barrier. Follow the gravel road until the crag appears on your right. There's also an overgrown parking sign for the ancient fort. It's not known whether the road barrier is sometimes closed.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tumbo"
            ]
          }
        },
